Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Summer Student: Asset Management Simcoe , ON Description Norfolk County Public LibraryPosition: Summer Student: Asset Management Status: 35 hours per week temporary position (July 2, 2024 – August 30, 2024) Posting Period: June 6, 2024 – June 18, 2024 Hourly Rate: $16.55 per hour Knowledge and Skills Education Required: Currently enrolled in full-time studies at a community college or university; and returning to full-time studies in the following school term. Experience: Familiar with Asset Management, Facility Operations and municipal legislation such as the Ontario Building Code, Fire Code and Ontario Health and Safety Act preferred. Skills: Ability to work independently and effectively as a member of a team.Knowledge of Excel Program, and/or previous experience with database programs, data collection, entry and information research.Proficient use of Microsoft 365 with emphasis on Outlook, Excel, Word, Teams.Strong oral and written communication, public relations, and customer service skills.Previous research skills/experience and demonstrated abilities to be a creative problem solver would be an asset.Ability to travel to multiple NCPL Branch locations and have access to reliable transportation.Ability to multi-task, work with interruptions, be flexible, and work well under pressure to meet deadlines.Ability to interact and deal effectively and courteously with all levels of NCPL staff. Scope The Summer Student: Asset Management shall capture physical assets data by way of photographs, and identifiable metrics at the five library branches and enter obtained information into the Norfolk County developed spreadsheet and/or software. Working Relationships The Summer Student functions within the Facilities and Operations Manager’s reporting line, in keeping with the policies and procedures of the library system, and with respect to the guidelines and standards as set by the Library Board. The Summer Student: Asset Management will be supervised by the Collection Development and Technology Manager or CEO when required. Working Conditions Work is performed in a mix of office environment and other facilities spaces; however, site reviews will require access to reliable vehicle transportation and some physical demands. Considerable movement within each library branch. Schedule and locations subject to change. Normal hours of work are 35 hours per week, Monday to Friday. Impact of Error Failure to perform duties as required could lessen library service and cause frustration to staff, confuse services, and may result in unfavorable public relations. Responsibilities The Summer Student: Asset Management will perform any or all the following duties: Collecting and coordinating data into an asset inventory template, for the purpose of entry into the Municipality’s Asset Register Software. Recording asset inventory, under the provision of the County and the Library, with great attention to detail in an organized manner to be used in Asset Management Planning.Assisting in the development and implementation of the Municipality’s Asset Management program specific to the Norfolk County Public Library’s holding and use of County assets.Providing and maintaining a high degree of confidentiality and security of information at all times.Work in compliance with Occupational Health and Safety Act, and other applicable legislation, NCPL policies/procedures, practices, operational guidelines, and perform safe work practices. Providing regular updates to the Library Leadership GroupPerforming other duties as assigned. The Norfolk County Public Library is an Equal Opportunity Employer in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005 and the Ontario Human Rights Code. Should you require Code-protected accommodation, through any stage of the recruitment process, please make them known in advance. Resumes must be submitted through email, mail or in person to Richard Anderson, Facilities and Operations Manager. Norfolk County Public Library 46 Colborne St. S. Simcoe, ON N3Y 4H3 519-426-3506 ex. 1251 richard.anderson@norfolkcounty.ca Thank you for your interest in this position. However, only those to be interviewed will be contacted. Compensation $16.55 per hour Closes: 18 June, 2024 Norfolk County Public Library Simcoe , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
