Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Supervisor, Customer Experience NEWMARKET , ON Description Overview of position Under the direction of the Manager, Library Services, the Supervisor, Customer Experience is responsible for the day-to-day delivery of efficient operations of the customer service and circulation functions of Library Services with specific responsibilities and a primary focus on promoting positive customer experiences throughout the library and its services. You are responsible for evaluating customer experience and champions customer service, playing a significant role in the continued development of Newmarket Public Library’s service delivery. Duties and Responsibilities •Provide supervision and coordination for staff in the implementation of annual business and work plans, for the Newmarket Public Library. Supervise staff and day-to-day administration of the customer service and circulation functions. •Oversees/coordinate staff development, coaching/mentoring and performance management. •Provide input to senior staff in the assessment of staffing needs, organizational structure changes, coordination and assignment of new services initiatives, recruitment of positions, discipline and termination. •Responsible for ensuring the delivery of the activities of the Newmarket Public Library and ensuring that the activities meet the goals and directions set by the Town of Newmarket. •Implements the Newmarket Public Library business plans in a timely proactive manner that is results oriented and meets the goals and objectives of the Library Services. •Liaise with the public to handle conflicts and issues with the goals of ensuring a positive customer experience for those using the public library. •Contact and liaison with community stakeholders, contractors, and vendors. •Requires leadership skills to coordinate and analyze daily workflow at critical service points; ensures effective and efficient use of staff resources, scheduling. •Liaises with and coordinates all public service staff training; oversees ongoing upgrading of public service employee technical skills. •Results oriented and meets the goals and objectives of the Library Services. Credentials Required Completion of an accredited Library and Information Technician Diploma with related experience of 3 to five years; or approved demonstrated combination of education and experience.Demonstrated supervisory skills to create and maintain a positive work environment, open communication, teamwork, respect, and trust.Understanding of system-wide public library functions and services, customer service experience, internal library processes, and activities.Ability to deal cooperatively and effectively with staff in a unionized environment, and with the public.Strong interpersonal, consultative, and public relations skills. Demonstrated solid communications skills with a focus on customer service and customer experience. Demonstrated writing skills to prepare reports, as well as revisions to training materials, processes and procedures.Demonstrated knowledge of budget preparation and management.Proficient in the use of MS Office (i.e. Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook) with a good understanding of library information systems and software application.May be required to work outside normal business hours, on occasion as required.Knowledge of applicable legislation, bylaws, legal proceedings and the ability to interpret legislation such as Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA), Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act (MFIPPA), Occupational Health and Safety Act and the Employment Standards Act. Hours of work 35 hours a week including evening and weekend shifts. Wages/Benefits Grade 8, $78,202-93,097 How to apply Submit a cover letter and resume to: https://newmarket.hua.hrsmart.com/hr/ats/JobSearch/viewAll.We thank all applicants for their interest. However, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Newmarket Public Library is committed to accommodating all applicants in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights Code for all employment activities including the recruitment process. The Newmarket Public Library is committed to a barrier-free recruitment and selection process. We uphold our values of diversity, equity, inclusion and anti-racism in the delivery of our services and in our workplace. The Library encourages applications from all applicants, including members of groups with historical employment barriers to equity, this is including but not limited to, Indigenous, Black and Racialized Groups, People with Disabilities, Women and Persons within the 2SLGBTQ+ community. Compensation $78,202-$93,097 Closes: 17 June, 2024 Newmarket Public Library NEWMARKET , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
